# CMS Admin Corrections — Profile Separation and Site Logo Upload

Two issues have been identified.

## Issue 1 — Admin Profile Is Using Investor Treatment

The `/profile` screen currently displays as an Investor Area profile screen.

This is wrong for admin users.

Admin profile and investor profile must not feel like the same experience.

### Required correction

If the authenticated user is an admin, the profile screen should use an admin/CMS-oriented layout.

Admin profile should show:

- Admin / CMS context
- Website CMS label
- Profile Information
- Update Password
- Delete Account if currently available
- No Investor Area branding
- No investor sidebar language
- No investment navigation
- No investor account label

Investor users may continue using the investor profile layout.

### Rule

Do not break investor profile.

Use role-based layout selection if needed.

---

## Issue 2 — Site Settings Missing Logo Upload

The CMS currently has no visible place to change or upload the site logo.

This is required.

### Required correction

Update the CMS Site Settings screen to include upload fields for:

- Site logo
- Inverse logo
- Favicon
- Default Open Graph image if already part of SiteSetting

Each upload field should include:

- current preview
- file input
- accepted types: jpg, jpeg, png, webp, svg where appropriate
- max size validation
- stored media relationship or current Media model pattern

### Site Settings should also expose

- Site name
- Tagline
- Primary email
- Phone
- Address
- Office hours
- Social links
- Footer text
- Copyright
- Default meta title
- Default meta description

### Rules

- Do not redesign the public site.
- Do not touch investor dashboard logic.
- Do not remove existing CMS fields.
- Do not bypass the Media model if the CMS already uses it.
- Do not create duplicate logo systems.
- Keep this inside the existing custom admin architecture.

---

